description: The architectural graph of CodeBoarding illustrates the end‑to‑end workflow that converts raw source code into semantic diagrams. The Orchestration & Planning component acts as the central controller, deciding whether to run a full or incremental analysis and delegating tasks to the Semantic Analysis Agents. These agents leverage the Static Analysis & Repository Tools to extract concrete code structures and control‑flow data, then pass their AI‑generated insights to the Semantic Validation & Quality layer for verification. The Incremental Update Engine monitors Git changes to limit re‑analysis, while the validated model is handed to the Visualization & Output Generation component for JSON and diagram rendering. Throughout, the Infrastructure & Persistence layer provides registries, plugin loading, and caching to support efficient operation.

components.name: Orchestration & Planning
components.description: Acts as the central controller of the system. It manages the high-level execution flow using a Meta Agent for project-wide context and a deterministic Planner to decide which components require deeper expansion based on structural complexity.

components.name: Prompt Factory Orchestrator
components.description: A central registry and factory that maps the configured LLMType to a concrete provider implementation. It decouples the core agent logic from model-specific prompt construction.

components.name: Structured Schema Registry
components.description: Defines the Pydantic-based contracts that ensure LLM outputs are structured and valid for downstream processing (e.g., persistence in DuckDB or visualization in Mermaid.js).

components.name: Anthropic & DeepSeek Adapters
components.description: Implements specialized prompt logic for Claude and DeepSeek models, focusing on cluster grouping and instruction styles unique to these providers.

components.name: OpenAI Adapter
components.description: Manages prompt templates optimized for GPT models, leveraging system messages and embedded JSON schemas for high-fidelity instruction following.

components.name: Google Gemini Adapter
components.description: Provides prompt engineering tailored for Gemini Flash, specifically handling file classification and meta-information prompts within Gemini's token constraints.

components.name: Regional Model Adapters (GLM & Kimi)
components.description: Encapsulates prompt generation for GLM and Kimi models, adapting to their specific tokenization, conversational patterns, and system-message conventions.

components.name: Semantic Analysis Agents
components.description: Specialized AI agents that interpret code data. The Abstraction Agent performs high-level grouping and pattern identification, while the Details Agent extracts implementation logic and fine-grained relationships for specific components.

components.name: Abstraction Agent
components.description: Orchestrates the macro-analysis phase of the semantic pipeline. It identifies high-level patterns and architectural themes by grouping disparate code entities into cohesive clusters. It defines the logical boundaries and "big picture" context required for downstream processing.

components.name: Details Agent
components.description: Orchestrates the micro-analysis phase. It performs granular extraction of implementation logic, method-level interactions, and specific component behaviors within the clusters defined by the Abstraction Agent. It transforms raw structural data into semantic technical descriptions.

components.name: Static Analysis & Repository Tools
components.description: The "senses" of the system. This component wraps LSP capabilities and custom static analysis to extract Control Flow Graphs (CFGs), package relationships, and method invocations, providing the objective data used by AI agents.

components.name: Static Analysis Engine
components.description: The core logic for resolving symbol references and qualified names (QNames). It ensures source code reference accuracy, providing the "ground truth" for all downstream analysis.

components.name: Agent Tooling Interface
components.description: The primary interface for AI agents. It wraps complex static analysis tasks into standardized tools (e.g., reading CFGs or structure) that agents use to "see" the codebase.

components.name: Repository Discovery Service
components.description: Scans the file system to map the project structure. It identifies internal dependencies and configuration files, providing the spatial context of the repository.

components.name: Semantic Abstraction Layer
components.description: Groups low-level CFG nodes into logical architectural components and subgraphs. It sanitizes data for visualization (Mermaid.js) and high-level reasoning.

components.name: Plugin Orchestrator
components.description: Dynamically loads and initializes analysis modules and agent tools. This allows the system to extend support for new languages or analysis types without core modifications.

components.name: LSP Client Wrapper
components.description: Manages communication with Language Servers (Python, TS, Java, etc.). It leverages the Language Server Protocol to retrieve precise definitions and references.

components.name: CFG Extractor
components.description: Generates detailed Control Flow Graphs from source code, identifying method invocations and execution paths within specific functions.

components.name: Dependency Resolver
components.description: Maps external and internal package relationships. It validates imports and builds the macro-level dependency graph of the repository.

components.name: Incremental Update Engine
components.description: Optimizes analysis by tracking changes via Git. It analyzes the impact of file modifications on the existing architectural model and orchestrates scoped re-analysis to avoid redundant LLM calls.

components.name: Incremental Orchestrator
components.description: The central controller of the incremental update lifecycle. It manages the workflow sequence: detecting repository changes, determining which architectural components are "dirty," and coordinating between lightweight metadata patching and heavyweight AI re-analysis.

components.name: File Change Manager
components.description: Interfaces with the version control system (Git) to classify raw file deltas into structured categories (additions, deletions, modifications, and renames). It maps these file-level changes to the existing architectural model.

components.name: Component State Checker
components.description: Evaluates the "dirtiness" of components based on the classified changes. It decides the processing path for each affected entity: whether it requires a full LLM-driven semantic re-analysis or can be handled via simple path updates.

components.name: Scoped Analysis Engine
components.description: Executes targeted AI agent workflows to re-analyze only the specific components identified as dirty. It generates new semantic descriptions and relationship data, ensuring the manifest reflects the latest code state without re-processing the entire codebase.

components.name: Manifest Manager
components.description: Serves as the subsystem's source of truth and persistence layer. It manages the loading of the existing architectural state (AnalysisManifest) and the saving of the updated model after an incremental run.

components.name: Path Patching Utility
components.description: A performance-optimization component that performs lightweight updates to file references and metadata for moved or renamed files. This avoids the high cost and latency of LLM re-analysis for structural changes that don't alter semantic meaning.

components.name: Visualization & Output Generation
components.description: Transforms internal semantic models into user-facing artifacts. It generates structured JSON representations and visual diagrams (e.g., Mermaid.js) depicting the multi-level hierarchy of the system.

components.name: Unified Analysis Orchestrator
components.description: Acts as the central facade for the subsystem. It coordinates the construction of the final report by integrating metadata, coverage data, and component hierarchies into a single cohesive artifact.

components.name: Structural Normalizer
components.description: Ensures graph consistency for visualization by performing recursive tree traversals to assign unique identifiers and rekeying analysis data.

components.name: Hierarchy Analyzer
components.description: Enriches the analysis by calculating structural metrics, specifically determining the nesting depth levels of components to enable multi-level hierarchical positioning in diagrams.

components.name: JSON Schema DTOs
components.description: Defines the formal data contracts (e.g., RelationJson, ComponentJson, UnifiedAnalysisJson) used for persistence and consumption by downstream AI agents and UI components.

components.name: Diagram Generator
components.description: The core engine that transforms internal semantic models and normalized JSON data into Mermaid.js syntax for visual representation.

components.name: Semantic Validation & Quality
components.description: A quality‑assurance layer that validates AI‑generated semantic insights against the ground truth from static analysis, ensuring that component relationships and file assignments are factually consistent.

components.name: Semantic Integrity Engine
components.description: The primary validator responsible for cross-referencing AI-generated metadata, naming conventions, and code relationships against the actual symbol tables and CFGs. It ensures that proposed abstractions and relationships are factually supported by the source code and aggregates validation findings for agent self-correction.

components.name: Incremental Consistency Guard
components.description: A specialized controller that manages the validation of partial updates. It filters incoming changes to ensure that incremental modifications to a diagram do not introduce global inconsistencies or violate existing structural rules, orchestrating the incremental validation workflow and optimizing performance.

components_relations.relation: forwards filtered, relevant code changes to the engine for deep semantic and relationship verification

components.name: Infrastructure & Persistence
components.description: Provides foundational services including a global registry for tool discovery, plugin loading, and multi-level caching of raw data and LLM responses to optimize performance.

components.name: Registry & Plugin Manager
components.description: Implements the Plugin/Registry pattern to provide a thread-safe, centralized discovery mechanism. It dynamically loads internal and external plugins at runtime to populate global registries, enabling decoupled system extension.

components.name: Tool Provisioning Engine
components.description: Orchestrates the discovery and resolution of external static analysis binaries (LSP servers). It manages the full lifecycle of these tools, including automated downloading and environment configuration when assets are missing.

components.name: Semantic Caching & Persistence
components.description: Manages incremental analysis by fingerprinting source files and LLM prompts. It uses a multi-level caching strategy to detect staleness and avoid redundant AI processing, utilizing a low-level storage interface for physical I/O.

components.name: Configuration Provider
components.description: Centralizes the management of user-specific settings, environment variables, and LLM provider credentials. It serves as the single source of truth for system-wide operational parameters.
